Based on the current policies, Belgium intends to phase out coal and nuclear. Hence, we suppose coal and nuclear power plants are shut down in 2035; thus not available. However, in the sensitivity analysis conducted in “Sensitivity Analysis of the System’s EROI” section, the installed nuclear capacity is considered an uncertain parameter. A limit of 27.9% (Limpens et al. 2020) of the 2035 electricity end-use demand, representing 27.57 [TWh/y], bounds the electricity imports and restricts the Belgian electrical dependence on neighboring countries. This study assumes an upper limit of 59.2 GWe (Limpens et al. 2020) of PV installed capacity. This estimation relies on two hypotheses: (i) the actual area of available well-oriented roofs is approximatively 250 km2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
