				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^2$$\end{document} (Devogelaer et al. 2012), which is around 1% of total Belgian lands; (ii) a 23% PV efficiency expected in 2035 with an average daily total irradiation, similar to historical values, of 2820 Wh/m2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
