				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{CO_2}$$\end{document}-eq./y]. Renewable fuels almost completely replace the PV and wind resources, and the system is partially un-electrified to use them. For instance, electric vehicles (mobility private and freight) are replaced by vehicles using synthetic fuels. That case is purely hypothetical because it assumes that (1) imported renewable fuels imply lower GHG emissions than renewable resources such as solar and wind. However, the GWP data on renewable fuels are not mature enough to draw such conclusions; (2) importing such large quantities of renewable fuels (approximately 510 [TWh/y]) may be unrealistic.Fig. 5
